Parliament, Friday, 11 October 2019 – The Chairpersons of the Standing Committee on Finance, Mr Joe Maswanganyi, and the Select Committee on Finance, Mr Yunus Carrim, invite stakeholders and other interested parties to forward written submissions on the 2019 Revised Fiscal Framework and Revenue Proposals, also known as the Medium Term Budget Policy Statement (MTBPS), which will be tabled by the Minister of Finance on 30 October 2019.
	
	Minister Mboweni will table the MTBPS in terms of section 28 of the Public Management Act 1 of 1999, which requires the Minister to table multi-year budget projections for revenue, expenditure and key macro-economic projections on an annual basis, as well as section 6 (1) of the Money Bills Amendment Procedure and Related Matters Act 9 of 2019.
	
	Mr Maswanganyi and Mr Carrim have advised those making written submissions to indicate their interest to make oral presentation during the public hearings, which will be held on 6 November 2019.
	
	All submissions should reach the committee by no later than 12:00 on Tuesday, 5 November 2019. They can be addressed either by post to the Committee Secretaries, Mr Allen Wicomb and Mr Nonkululeko Mangweni at 3rd floor, 90 Plein Street, Cape Town 8000, or by email to awicomb@parliament.gov.za and nmangweni@parliment.gov.za. Enquiries can be made telephonically on 021 403 3759 and 021 403 3782 or by fax on 021 403 3942.
	
	ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON FINANCE, MR JOE MASWANGANYI, AND CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON FINANCE, MR YUNUS CARRIM
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact Media Officer:
